Synopsis:
   set status_oper [<text>]

Description:
   This variable sets the string displayed in the status bar when the user
   has irc operator status (user mode +o).  If the client is not an irc
   operator, nothing is shown.

   This string is represented as %* in the STATUS_FORMAT string.  It is
   treated literally inside STATUS_OPER.

Examples:
   Setting the string displayed when the client has operator status:
      /set status_oper *

See Also:
   oper(3); set(4) status_format

